+When mapping question tokens to schema objects, always surface lookup targets and exact spellings: 1) If a column name looks like an FK (ends with _id) or FK metadata exists, include the referenced table name, its human-readable column(s) (e.g. colour.colour, publisher.publisher_name), and 3 sample_rows from that table. 2) Prioritize tables whose sample values lexically match question entities (e.g. 'color','name','language'). 3) Explicitly list any columns with spaces or unusual punctuation and show exact sample values and the exact column header so SQLWriter can quote them. 4) For each matched id column produce a one-line mapping: FK_column -> referenced_table(human_column) and provide sample values. 5) Always hand off: exact column spellings, quoted names if needed, and the small sample_rows for any lookup tables.
 
